@node PPS40-28-XXX31 "Module PPS 040/2000"
    @{fg highlight}Module PPS 040/2000 :@{fg text}

@{i}Yann-Erick Proy @{ui}@{fg fill}yann-erick.proy@imag.fr@{fg text}

Modules obtained with a  A2000 B  (6.2 revision),  a GVP HCD II + 4 MB RAM
expansion (SCSI controller),  a GVP SR-2 2 MB RAM expansion (SCSI control-
ler)  and a  28 MHz PPS 040/2000 board  fitted with  8 MB 32 bits RAM  (of
which 2 in AUTOCONFIG space).

@{b} For the two first modules :@{ub}

The dynamic library  @{b}68040.library@{ub}  isn't the one  delivered  with the 3.1
Kickstart  (40.63)  but the one delivered with the board  (system software
dated august 1992...)  :  but for that it is impossible to use the @{u}Init040@{uu}
program to add the memory blocks outside AUTOCONFIG space to the available
memory.

It seems impossible  to get stable operation  if the whole PPS 32 bits RAM
is outside AUTOCONFIG space.

It has been impossible  to relocate the 3.1 Kickstart  in RAM with the @{b}CPU
FASTROM@{ub} command from the 3.1 system : it has no effect.

@{b} For the next modules :@{ub}

The system software provided by PPS  is replaced by @{u}Set040@{uu} 2.41  for 68040
control and  @{u}AddMem 3.01@{uu},  eventually @{u}ROMTagMem 3@{uu},  for taking the 32 bits
RAM into account.  This way, the 68040.library from the 3.1 Kickstart runs
perfectly, and the Kickstart is relocatable in RAM. Furthermore, the whole
32 bits memory  can stay outside  AUTOCONFIG,  but the system is  a little
slower.

Various @{"patches" link PatchSofts} supposed  to accelerate the system have been tried,  other
than @{u}Set040@{uu}, @{u}AddMem@{uu} or @{u}ROMTagMem@{uu} : @{u}CopyMemQuicker@{uu} and @{u}FBL@{uu} 6.6.

@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-ROM31            @{fg text} KS 3.1
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-ROM31-NoAutocfg  @{fg text} no AUTOCONFIG 32 bits RAM, KS 3.1
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-FAS31            @{fg text} KS 3.1 in RAM
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-FAS31-CpMemQk    @{fg text} CopyMemQuicker, KS 3.1 in RAM
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-FAS31-FBL66      @{fg text} FBL 6.6, KS 3.1 in RAM
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-FAS31-ROMTag     @{fg text} ROMTag 3, KS 3.1 in RAM
@{fg highlight}PPS40-28-FAS31-ROMTagFBL  @{fg text} ROMTag 3, FBL 6.6, KS 3.1 in RAM
@endnode

