@rem ----------------------------------------- So called humour nodes



@node Amiga "Amiga"
    @{fg highlight}Amiga :@{fg text} the computer for the creative mind.

Being creative means necessarily turn one's back to established standards,
which answer to a motivation of productivity, and experiment, sometimes to
it's own detriment, something new.

This is the reason why  one shouldn't then  fall into  the trap of  devout
fanaticism, creativity desert since broad-mindedness is bannished from it.


This being said...

  I piss upon short-winded Macintoshes and stinking Windows PCs !!!

(Thanks Bar2...)
@endnode

@node 80486 "80486"
    @{fg highlight}80486 :@{fg text} Of course not.

The 80486 is a @{"ROTTEN" link Rotten} processor,  that may be found in these @{"ROTTEN" link Rotten} micros
called PC,  and animated (well, it's a mode of speaking...) by this @{"ROTTEN" link Rotten}
system of MS-DOS, flanked by its Windows wart, @{"ROTTEN" link Rotten} to the bone !

And I don't even mention the Pentium,  which can't align  a division and a
multiplication with float numbers.

  @{i}The brand new Pentium technology : floating arithmetics.
  Intel : still ahead !@{ui}

  @{i}CAUTION ! Intel inside !@{ui}
@endnode

@node Rotten "The Amiga is a machine for enthusiastics : up and at tolerants !"
    @{fg highlight}PCs are rotten machines :@{fg text} Yes, of course yes.

You disagree ?!? Uh ? Well... Aren't you @{"Cédric" link CedricBeust} by chance ?
@endnode

@node CedricBeust "Cédric Beust"
    @{fg highlight}Cédric Beust :@{fg text} Uh, who's that ?

For some people :

Brilliant Jack-of-all-trades of the Amiga in France,  regular and inspired
contributor  to the french magazine  "Amiga News"  (75 published articles,
since the issue #9,  where he was unassembling the SCA virus),  founder of
the french  speaking mailing-list "@{fg fill}amiga@sophia.inria.fr@{fg text}", author of XData
(data management mechanism via IFFParse.library)... In short, a great name
of the Amiga close to Giorgo Cuppertino, Fred Fish, Urban Dominik Mueller,
etc

For the others :

Pretentious INRIA researcher, dangerous revisionist inviting to forget the
Amiga  for looking to  the  PC side,  dark prophet  of the Amiga  collapse
preaching the most  discouraging catastrophism...  In short a wicked indi-
vidual to pillory, close to Bill Gates, Marc Barret, etc

The ones and the others thus betray the @{"influence" link Amen} that Cédric has over the
french Amiga community.
@endnode

@node PC "PC : Purulent Cart"
    @{fg highlight}PC :@{fg text} BEEEEEUUUUUUUUARK ! Hum ! Excuse-me...
@endnode

@node Amen "Personnal thought... Don't read."
    @{fg highlight}Personnal thought... :@{fg text} Don't read.

After such an epitaph,  I think I gained the right to rag him  one hundred
times (at least) on Usenet without being excluded from the mailing list...
I believed I had tell you not to read !
@endnode

@node AIBBStupid "You were there, booby..."
    @{fg highlight}AIBB :@{fg text} Say, do you believe we're goin' to turn round like that for long ?
@endnode

@node SadicLionel "Rough handling..."
    @{fg highlight}Rough handling :@{fg text} a 25 MHz 68030 overclocked to 40 MHz

After having plagued his playmates for long  that with his @{i}40 MHz@{ui} hot-shot
he was overspeeding everybody, Lionel realized that he had lost the @{i}MMU @{ui}on
his way : no Enforcer or virtual memory (VMM), not much Unix...

The @{i}monster@{ui} then recovered, in old scrap Sun workstations, some unlucky @{i}25 @{ui}
@{i}MHz 68030,@{ui}  who were thinking to be able  to enjoy a well deserved retire-
ment.  After having @{i}wrung@{ui} more than one of these devices, he found out one
being more enduring, and, since then, @{i}cruelly @{ui}force it to run at @{i}40 MHz@{ui}.
@endnode

@node PhB "Philippe Brand"
    @{fg highlight}Philippe Brand :@{fg text} world's GNU order

Dynamic french salesman of the @{i}Macrosystems @{ui}company  and world-wide sales-
man of @{i}GNU @{ui}for the Amiga branch,  Philippe has the advantage to experience
a very comfortable situation,  since the @{i}Retina BLTZ3 @{ui}board  is the unique
graphics board available for the Amiga and  @{u}GCC@{uu} is the unique C++ compiler
for the Amiga (or is it for any computer ?)...

Displaying an @{i}examplary willingness @{ui}despite of an overloaded daily routine
this sympathetic  and @{i}persuasive @{ui}Amiga adept  is also sysop of the  @{i}Ramses @{ui}
BBS (the only one for Amiga in France...)  and @{u}NetBSD@{uu} promotor (the unique
Amiga UNIX...).

One can wonder if his Amiga  is not the only one world-wide to be program-
mable in "wooden language" !

  @{i}Keep cool, have a nice @{"beer" link StayDrunk !@{ui}
@endnode

@node StayDrunk "Personnal thought... Don't read."
    @{fg highlight}Personnal thought... :@{fg text} Don't read.

About that matter,  the first time I meet Philippe will probably cost me a
fortune in beers of many brands...
@endnode

@node JLManchon "Jean-Luc Manchon"
    @{fg highlight}Jean-Luc Manchon :@{fg text} Multi-tasking neuron

Author of @{u}Synapse@{uu}, a french AmigaGuide database about the Amiga (with many
details  and even motherboards  schematics !),  Jean-Luc is among  the few
ones who sent me a bug report for CompilAIBB...

Fortunately exists mountain folk fellowship !


    @{u}Synapse@{uu}, available on @{"Aminet" link Aminet} or @{u}DPAT@{uu} 90.
@endnode



@rem -------------------- This one should have been a humour node too

@node PierreCarrette "Pierre Carrette"
    @{fg highlight}Pierre Carrette :@{fg text} inspired Amiga developper

Co-author,  with Sylvain Rougier,  of many very  smart Amiga software  and
regular  intervener  on  the  french  mailing-list  @{fg fill}amiga@sophia.inria.fr@{fg text},
Pierre  stunned  me by his inner  understanding  of the  Amiga programming
style.

Just try these packages and you will share my opinion for sure :

@{u}BrowserII@{uu}         multi-windows, multitasking, compact file manager
@{u}ParM@{uu}              for launching programs from WorkBench with menus
@{u}ObjectArchive@{uu}     for accessing tar or lha archives as any disk device
@{u}WhatIs@{uu}            file content recognition library

Unfortunately, Pierre, who not only showed good technical capabilities but
rare human qualities, has leaved us,  on his motorbike, during the evening
of Wednesday, May 12, 1995.

Farewell,  Pierre,  I won't forget  these almost  two years of  electronic
friendliness, and courage, Sylvain.
@endnode

